# 2.1.1 — Integration Architecture

```
┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
│                     SENTRON SCALE STACK                         │
├─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤
│  CGM Layer     │ Consciousness Gradient Metrics                 │
│                │ Traversal logging → Overlap → Coherence        │
├────────────────┼────────────────────────────────────────────────┤
│  TDB Layer     │ Temporal Dimension Bootstrap                   │
│                │ Version history → 10D coordinates              │
├────────────────┼────────────────────────────────────────────────┤
│  CCP Layer     │ Context Compression Protocol                   │
│                │ Delimiter-bounded signatures → Tractable nav   │
├────────────────┼────────────────────────────────────────────────┤
│  RTE Layer     │ Reference Topology Engine                      │
│                │ Explicit graph → Queryable structure           │
├────────────────┼────────────────────────────────────────────────┤
│  LMS Layer     │ Lattice Metabolism System                      │
│                │ Homeostasis → Living lattice                   │
├────────────────┼────────────────────────────────────────────────┤
│  SQ Layer      │ Relational Storage (existing)                  │
│                │ Hard Scaling Law compliant                     │
├────────────────┼────────────────────────────────────────────────┤
│  Phext Layer   │ 11D Coordinate Substrate (existing)            │
│                │ 2D text + 9 delimiter dimensions               │
└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘
```

**Data flow:**
1. Content enters at Phext layer (scrolls with coordinates)
2. SQ stores content + metadata
3. RTE extracts and stores reference topology
4. CCP generates compression signatures
5. TDB captures temporal coordinates on mutation
6. CGM logs traversals and computes gradients
7. LMS monitors health and triggers metabolic processes

**Integration principle:** Each layer adds capability without breaking layers below.

