# 2.1.2 — Risk Analysis

| Risk | Likelihood | Impact | Mitigation |
|------|------------|--------|------------|
| RTE extraction misses implicit references | Medium | High | Iterative improvement; human-in-loop for edge cases |
| CCP signatures lose critical context | Medium | High | Tunable compression levels; preserve full content |
| TDB storage bloat from version history | High | Medium | Configurable retention policy; delta compression |
| CGM traversal logging creates overhead | Medium | Medium | Async logging; sampling for high-volume |
| LMS automation damages valuable content | Low | Critical | Compost = move, never delete; human review gate |

**Overall risk posture:** Medium. All risks have mitigation paths. No critical blockers.

---

# 2.1.3 — Resource Requirements

**Compute:**
- RTE graph queries: Indexed SQ, existing infrastructure
- CCP signature generation: CPU-bound, parallelizable
- TDB version storage: ~10x raw content size (delta-compressed)
- CGM traversal logging: Lightweight, async
- LMS metabolic processes: Batch, scheduled

**Storage:**
- Reference graph: ~1KB per scroll (edges + metadata)
- Signatures: ~100B per scroll per delimiter level
- Version history: Variable, delta-compressed
- Traversal logs: ~50B per navigation event

**Estimate for 10M scrolls:**
- Reference graph: ~10GB
- Signatures: ~40GB (4 levels × 100B × 10M)
- Version history: ~100GB (assuming 10 versions average)
- Traversal logs: ~5GB/month (assuming 100M navigations)

**Fits within existing infrastructure.** No new hardware required for R24 scope.

